value.0: "Were you wanting another of The Stan's exciting quests, or were you wondering about the election?"
"Now, The Stan is positive you will be wanting to go to our enemy's hideout. Good day to you, my <lord/lady>."
"You have completed all of The Stan's quests for now. Best of luck in the election."
The large half orc stands laughing with a couple of friends. As you approach he turns and smiles cheerfully.
"Looks like another young scallywag has come to test their mettle on a challenging quest from The Stan."
"The Stan said you were a scallywag... not in an unfriendly way though. The Stan merely thinks you look like the type of person who enjoys a good adventure."
"The Stan? Do you not recognize the superiority of The Stan? Are you not humbled by the very presence of The Stan? The Stan is insulted. What a grievous wound indeed!"
"The Stan! You haven't heard of The Stan? Well, The Stan is insulted. What a grievous wound indeed!"
"But The Stan is strong and resilient! The Stan can take the insults of low minded individuals and ignore them as the sting of a wasp."
"Bees sting... wasps bite."
"Are you a wasp? No, The Stan does not think so. Do not presume to know more than The Stan, for that would be true folly."
"Are you looking for adventure, or are you here about the election?"
"The Stan wishes you safe journeys."
"The Stan knows now who was foolish enough to steal from The Stan. The Stan hopes that you have learned your lesson and will respect the sanctity of The Trades store."

value.0: "The Stan is happy to serve those who show The Stan the respect he is due."
"The Stan's knowledge of all things in the keep is unparalleled, and you show wisdom in coming to The Stan for his advice."
"The Stan is glad to have had this chance to enlighten you. Is there anything else The Stan can help you with?"
"The Stan stood on the walls and fought their ilk, and their brutish ways were no match for the unmatched capabilities of The Stan."
"Most fled from The Stan's terrible wrath, for it was a frightening thing to behold. Should they come again, The Stan shall meet them and throw them back again."
"The Stan would suggest the Silver Lily, in the north keep. It is a place of refinement and sweet sustenance. The Stan would also suggest you purchase a house from Serah."
"Glassy has, in the opinion of The Stan, formidable weapons and armor. That is where The Stan would send you."
"The Stan runs the Trades Guild. Why would you ask such a foolish question? All come to The Stan with quests."
"That is what The Stan's mother named him. What else should The Stan call himself?"
"The Stan's mother never spoke directly to The Stan, she would just say things like 'The Stan had better clean his room,' and The Stan would obey."
"The Stan's mother was none too proud of The Stan's orcish father. But that is fine, for The Stan is strong and is none too proud of his mother."
"But this is a topic which The Stan no longer wishes to discuss. So choose another topic from which you would gain insights from The Stan."
"The Stan is the foremost authority for the trades guild. The Stan has keen understanding of the three contenders. What would you ask of him?"

"Sir Becket hired some of The Stan's tradesmen to refurbish his mansion. Sir Becket took over a year to pay his debts off. This filled The Stan with great anger."
"The next time Sir Becket has to have something fixed, The Stan will not be supplying him with labor."
"Having a strong leader who knows how to enforce the law is important for the trades. If people fear for their lives or their wealth then employment suffers."
"Enivid is the epitome of law. The Stan knows there are problems she will encounter, but she could learn to adapt."

value.0: "The Stan knows that adventure isn't for everyone. How else can The Stan, in his infinite wisdom, assist you?"
"Good, which of The Stan's fine adventures would you care to enjoy?"
"Go speak to Alias as soon as you are ready to go."
"The farmers will be pleased when they see their herds again. If you get the cattle out of the caves, they should wander home."
"Speak to Alias when you are ready to go."
"The Stan is pleased and the dwarves shall be too. The Stan will inform the dwarves and all you need to do is return to me when you are done."
"Alias knows where the dwarves were mining, so she can lead you there."
"There are some who say that this keep was built on the ruins of another keep, and that the old, dark magic of an ancient empire yet lives on in these old stones."

"The most noted scholar in the north, Ohio Smith, has found an old ruin not far from here, but the place is infested with undead. If the stories are true, then the very fate of this keep might be contained within that ruin."
"Help the archeologist, and 1000 gold is yours. It is a princely sum, but a most dangerous and important task. Alias can lead you to him."
"Those foul yet clever lizard-kin, the kobolds, are supplying the Masked Man's army with food gathered from the poor peasants and landowners in the area."
"The farmers have come to ask that someone go and free their cows from the clutches of the cunning kobolds. And they offer 500 gold in return."
"The monsters have also stolen stores of grain, so you might be able to get the cows to follow you by using it. Alias can show you where their cave is."
"Imagine an adventure in the deepest, darkest mines, where foul, evil duergar have wrested control from their fairer kin. Where brutal, cunnning traps and vicious, challenging fights await you."

"This is one of the grand adventures The Stan has to offer you. A twisted and powerful mage leads the duergar and the dwarves would have you kill him, that they might drive their evil cousins from their home."
"The pay is 500 gold, but there is a magic weapon in it for you if you also kill the other duergar leaders. The mage is the main target, but you're welcome to do it all. What do you say?"
